OL,3,CPlaid Cymru launch General Election
OL,4,Cmanifesto with bid for #4bn HS2
OL,5,Ccompensation
OL,7,FPlaid Cymru has launched its General
OL,8,FElection manifesto, calling for fairer
OL,9,Ffunding for Wales including an extra
OL,10,F#4billion from the HS2 rail project.
OL,12,FRhun ap Iorwerth, the leader of the
OL,13,Fparty and a member of the Senedd,
OL,14,Flaunched the manifesto at an event in
OL,15,FCardiff on Thursday, 13 June.
OL,17,FThe party is calling for windfall
OL,18,Ftaxes on oil and gas companies, money
OL,19,F"owed to Wales" in rail funding and
OL,20,Ffor closer ties with the EU, which the
OL,21,Fcountry left following Brexit.
